The lack of snow in the mountains bothers hoteliers
The deserted pose no problem for operators of ski.
The lack of snow discourages people to book their stays in hotels and pensions.
As a result, it is always possible to find free rooms for all dates in winter, including Christmas and New Year.
We have a lot of hits on our site.
Internet users roam offers, asking prices but dare not commit to set aside for the moment.
And if they call us, they call immediately if there will be snow or mud at Christmas, "said Martin Jandura, operator of the information portal Spindl.Info.
If you want to spend New Year's Eve of his dreams to Špindlerův Mlýn, better not too reluctant to book.
If it gives priority to economies and that the quality of accommodation comes next, then we can try to wait a few more days.
The hotel will offer Špindler for the moment that stays a week for the New Year.
I think they will try one more time to place, but they also and accept shorter periods.
And then the number of rooms free will rapidly diminish, "said Jandura.
The agency's tourism Ingtours Vrchlabí also proposes yet beds free for all periods of winter.
The week of Christmas interests us most at the moment, it is not completely sold.
There are still free, say, half of the rooms in our offer.
That is why we have already prepared some last-minute Christmas holidays cheaper, "said the director of Ingtours Petr schiefert.
The agency Vrchlabí tourism may also propose the New Year to Krkonoše, but there are fewer empty seats.
The 14 days of February go well, stays hivernaux remaining sell moderately.
This year, the interest for stays of winter has been negatively influenced by the fact that there is still no snow Krkonoše.
People expect it to fall.
Nobody wants to spend the winter in the mountains.
If the tracks overlap during the week, Christmas also will be complete, "think Schiefert.
Conversely, the occupation of the Hotel Horizont Pec pod Sněžkou is slightly higher than last year.
It was an improvement of about five percent.
We still have a few places for the New Year as for Christmas.
There is a great interest during the holidays in January and February of Polish sells well too, "informs Karel Rada, director of the best hotel in Pec.
The hotel Omnia near central park of Jánské Lázně is also full of eighty percent during the period of the New Year.
On the contrary, half of the beds are empty at Christmas in the most recent hotel Jánské Lázně.
This year, we were pleasantly surprised by the month of January, where we have already sixty percent occupancy at present.
February is a bit lower for the moment, but as soon as the snow will fall, interest for stays in the Krkonoše grows still certainly said the director of the hotel Omnia, Erik Sporysch.
The hotel krkonoše should not expect more snow.
On Thursday it will be fresher and if there is rain, they should be neigeuses mountain.
But the time should warm, Jií Jakubský station of the Czech HydroMeteorological Institute.
United States: Repetition is the mother of wisdom "
It becomes even comical, the painstaking effort with which Barack obama, president of the reputation of wise, reproduced the strategy of his predecessor on the Afghan question, that he considered himself as simple.
When it came to leave its doctrine so hard, it turned out that he had in carbon paper since the Iraqi scenario of Bush from three years ago.
Not content to use in the text itself several times "as in Iraq," he has not hesitated, which is more, to use the title of the speech by Bush in January 2007 as the title of his own speech: "A new way forward."
At the same time, he has personally criticized the idea of Bush to send reinforcements in Iraq a consumed by the civil war as "irresponsible and a disastrous decision in its consequences."
The following month, however, have shown that the strategy of Bush, who came to the recommendations of commanders of campaigns, was the only possible and likely success to the point that the newspapers currently do not speak at all of Iraq.
This has not enhanced the reputation of Bush, however, objectively speaking, it was left to his successor a final situation much more favourable than we could have hoped.
Barack Obama hopes that in Afghanistan, the miracle will happen again
These are the commanders of campaigns that have requested an increase in the military contingent, including the commander of the operation in afghanistan, general Stanley mccristal, which has severely criticized the reluctance of the White House despite the habits of subordination.
He asked for 40,000 troops in order to make the situation more favourable.
The President has hesitated for three months but for lack of a better option, at least he had defrauded the General of 10,000 soldiers.
He has managed to stamp out the promise of additional 5,000 from Europe, even if it had about 10,000.
This brings the most problems throughout the strategy of Obama seems to be his intention to withdraw forces from Afghanistan within 18 months and finish this whole process within three years. Any doctrine of Obama raises more questions than it provides answers.
Many doubt the fact that an increase of half will bring the same fruit that progress in Iraq.
Despite the fratricidal wars in recent years, Iraqi society is relatively well organised and its leaders to honour the agreements.
The Afghan situation stands out for the exact opposite - we cannot rely on anyone and no treaty is respected.
In these conditions, difficult to prepare Afghan security forces, accustomed to change overnight leader depending on what suits them.
The political institutions, although based officially smokescreen behind which will proliferate ethnic relations.
It is extremely difficult to balance the interests of various ethnic groups given the lack of clarity on the reports, which are further complicated by the Pakistani and Iranian influences.
Even the foundation of a "quick to act", which is the basic aim of the operation, does not appear to be very real.
The time horizon of Obama's strategy he was perplexed by his proactive approach.
In the past eight years, the situation in Afghanistan has worsened and she is currently on the brink of chaos.
Only a heart purely romantic and out of the reality can be persuaded that the small soldiers sent to the tumult of the war in order to their "speedy return home" will bring a real miracle.
From a political point of view, set a date for the withdrawal of troops is purely irresponsible because the Taliban will see this as the indirect admission of defeat.
The last NATO summit has shown that Europeans want to participate in military operations in Afghanistan is moving to negative.
The European politicians don't know or do not want to explain to their constituents why security in Germany or Italy is linked to a war in the mountains of the Hindu Kush.
Another factor that could radically alter the situation is changing events related to Iran.
If the situation continues to deteriorate and enhanced penalties have no effect on the Iranians, the Americans will face the very difficult issue of a resolution of the problem by the use of military force.
It will respond by example when, according to Obama, America will come to the victorious withdrawal of troops from Afghanistan.
Each solution of this kind will, however, a dramatic reversal of the Afghan situation.
The only patch for Obama is the fact that there are still three years until the presidential elections and therefore there is still enough time for that it is working on a new strategy, if it proves to be a flop.
The leaders of the bank Goldman Sachs will no longer receive cash bonuses
Employees senior leaders of the US bank Goldman Sachs will no longer receive cash bonuses this year.
The company announced in response to strong criticism of its pay practices.
The group of 30 senior leaders will receive shares instead of money, they cannot resell within five years.
The actions can be taken to the leaders in case they would take too many risks.
According to Reuters, Goldman Sachs and is leading the effort to link pay with long-term performance on Wall Street.
I assume that Wall Street is well aware of the global sense that, "said the former investment banker Douglas Elliott of the company's takeover
The concern is in the details, "he added.
The bank Goldman Sachs has become the target of criticism after being set aside almost $17 billion in premiums on the first three quarters of this year.
For the year, the total amount of premiums will probably exceed $20 billion despite the announcement today, according to Reuters.
With the arrival of the financial crisis, large bonuses in the banking sector have become a sensitive political issue in many countries.
Britain announced Wednesday that it intends to spend a single fee of 50 per cent bankers' bonuses in excess of 25,000 pounds.
France is preparing similar measures.
This year women won the Nobel Prize in all areas except physics
These are five women, a record number, which have received today in Stockholm hands of Sweden's King Carl XVI Gustaf the Nobel Prize in the technical disciplines and literature.
In addition to the four scientists there was also German writer Herta Müller Romanian origin.
Two American biologists, Elizabeth Blackburn and Carol Greider received with their compatriot Jack Szostak the Nobel Prize for Medicine for their research in the field of chromosomes.
The prize for chemistry was awarded to the Israeli Ada Jonath with the Americans Venkatraman Ramakrishnan and Thomas Steitz for clarifying the structure and function of ribosomes
The last winner received the Nobel Prize in Economics, the American Elinor Ostrom with his fellow countryman Oliver Williamson, for their analysis of economic governance.
The only technical discipline that has not been winner this year was physics.
The prize was awarded today scientists Charles Kao for his research in the field of optical fibres and George Smith avecWillard Boyle for their invention of CCD chips, which are currently at the forefront of all digital cameras, fax or glasses astronomical.
Each winner received the diploma, the Nobel medal and certificate of acquisition of financial reward.
It reached 10 million Swedish crowns in each category. (approximately 1.1 million euros).
If one of them contains several winners, they will share the prize.
The much-anticipated Nobel Peace Prize has already been handed this afternoon in Oslo in Norway to US President Barack obama.
The latter, in his speech, acknowledged the controversial nature of his reward because it is only at the beginning of his journey and that it is in addition to the head of a country engaged in two wars in Iraq and Afghanistan.
In the discharge of its policy he added that in certain situations the war is essential to achieve peace, even if the price is high.
