Morgan Freeman will play Mandela in the new movie by Clint eastwood
Despite criticism of the fact that the main roles are played by American actors, South Africans say that the new Hollywood film Invictus - Invaincu will present the world a lot of things about the country, its struggles and victories.
The story about sport, relations between races and Nelson Mandela.
Morgan freeman, american actor rewarded at the oscars, embodies the film on the life of Nelson mandela, tireless fighter against the racist apartheid regime in South Africa and first black president.
Freeman said, that this is a Mandela aged who asked him to embody in the film.
Matt Damon plays an important role.
I told him: "If I play, I should be able to see you personally..
The actor seventy-two years old who was awarded a prize for his role in the drama limited Dollar Baby of Clint Eastwood located in the middle of boxing has, for example, embodied the leader of a movement against slavery itself become a slave, a fictional US president, even God in the film Evan Almighty but never someone still alive and also important for so many people that is Mandela.
The former South African statesman was jailed for 27 years for his hard work in favour of the end of apartheid in South Africa.
He was released in 1990 and became president of the country for four years.
In 1993 he was awarded the Nobel Peace Prize.
Invictus is a Latin word meaning unbeaten, and it is the title of a poem by the English author William Ernest Henley published in 1875.
The challenge was to speak with him.
The film tells The true story of The joint efforts of Nelson Mandela and The captain of The South African rugby team François to unify The country. The newly elected President Mandela resteencore and knows that his country still divided racially and economically after apartheid.
He is confident of being able to unite his people through sport and decides to unite the rugby players who are among the outsiders in the world.
The South African team will eventually move in World Cup in 1995.
Freeman has worked a few years to bring the history of Mandela on big screen.
I had no other purpose if not play this role to bring the reality, "said freeman.
The biggest challenge for me it was obviously talk like him
The actor said that if he and the international politician were in the same region, he would have tried to meet Mandela, dinner with him, to be behind the scenes before his speech.
The most important thing for him was to shake hands.
I realized that when I shake hands, I recover your energy, it is transmitted and I had the impression of how you feel, he said.
It is important for me to try to become another person.
Matt Damon plays in the film François Pienaar, the captain of a National Rugby team in which there is a majority of white players.
The actor said he had six months to prepare for a role in the harsh environment of rugby.
For him, his first meeting with Pienaar at his home was a great surprise.
I remember when I come to the door of the house, he opened and the first thing I said to Francois Pienaar was: 'I look a lot more in the film ".
Despite the differences between the real actors and models, Invictus under the leadership of the director Eastwood received positive notices and there is even talk of ambitions for the Oscars.
The film critic Todd McCarthy of Daily Variety summed up his appreciation in these words: "This is a very good story, a film very well done."
In the evaluations of films on the Web site rottentomatoes.com, Invictus received 76 percent of positive feedback.
The mystery of the aura in Norway is resolved: Russians tested a rocket
There has been a strange phenomenon of unknown origin above Norway.
The Russian Ministry of Defence has recognized that yesterday have tested a rocket intercontinental ballistic not far from the Norwegian border.
The launch has been a failure and the missile "bulava" which was originally scheduled to be the pride of the Russian army is gradually becoming the nightmare of Russian generals and Prime Minister Vladimir putin.
His presence repeated testing the rocket has not had the desired effect on the success of test flights.
Most of the time, Bulava has not disappeared, or it was damaged in mid-air.
The Russian newspapers talk of "Bulava" as the "missile which do not steal"
A missile that is not
This 13th test took place at the beginning as normal.
It was not until the end of the flight that there was further damage on the apparatus.
This is clearly the engine of the third floor of the rocket that exploded.
This time, "Bulava" flew nuclear submarine Dmitrij Donskij sailing under the surface of the White Sea.
This type of missile can be fired from a moving boat and
This is the reason for the mysterious light over Norway caused by an unidentified flying object apparently was a "defective".
Moreover, the norwegian did not doubt that it is a Russian rocket.
The generals argue that this time we cannot talk utter failure.
The first two floors of the rocket have resisted and damage was confined to third.
In previous cases, the engines have been failures on the first floor.
Although none of the test launches went smoothly, the direction of the Ministry of Defence considers that only six out of thirteen were failures.
The success rate of almost 50 per cent fills the general optimism and they say is always a day "Bulava'fly without problems and that it will even ten nuclear cores hypersoniques a total weight of 1.15 tonnes.
