According to the new schedules of the ČD there will be fewer trains for the same charges.
The czech Railways will prohibit or limit from 13 December some express trains or regional less responsible and instead would increase others.
The full coverage of transport will decline to date of entry into force of the new schedules of two percent compared to today.
Most of the charges will not change, including fares and cuts.
For example the inhabitants of the region in Ostrava who will have more connections to the capital, the Railways will add a rowing Pendolino.
On the contrary, an Express will cease to serve Bratislava.
There will also be less fast trains on the line Prague - Písek - České Budějovice, the direct line Prague - Letohrad will be drastically reduced.
At the regional level, the largest decrease in transport for the region of Hradec Králové eight percent in total, Prague and its environs can celebrate an increase.
Two night trains on the line Prague - Tábor - České Budějovice - are also cancelled and the movement of some express trains on the line Prague - Písek - České Budějovice - will amount to only a few days in the week.
Among the most sweeping changes, we can see the introduction of a new direct line of Milovice in prague: for the moment the inhabitants of Milovice must change to Lysá nad labem.
It is the fifteenth line of the commuter system Esko, whose opening is possible thanks to the completion of the electrification of the line between Lysá nad Labem and Milovice.
The distant lines to the capital will have their final destination at the main railway station in prague (Praha Hlavní nádraží).
The ČD will introduce more lines between Prague and Ostrava and SC Pendolino trains bound for šumperk/jeseník depart at intervals of two hours.
Travellers can no longer take the Pendolino up in Bratislava on 13 December.
The bill this year for regional railways: 200 million kroner.
The express trains are ordered and paid by The Ministry of Transport and The Railways next year by a total of four billion kroner to losses visible, The same amount as this year. The regional trains were ordered by The regions who will pay for them by a total of eight billion next year, knowing that The state will participate to The tune of almost three billion.
This year the regional trains are 200 million more expensive.
The railways have newly signed a contract for ten years, until now the duration was always a year.
The Railways appreciate the system, which also explains that they have not used a price increase of the vast majority of tickets.
The changes will affect only tickets a day ČD Net and the Internet eLiška tickets at reduced prices.
For travellers without reduction card, the price of ČD Net will increase from 450 to 600 crowns.
The price of eLiška newly will depend on the journey, whereas previously it was valid between the towns of a region to choice and was at a single rate of 160 crowns.
The Filipino rebels still hold more than 50 people, children have been released
The rebels have kidnapped today 75 people in the southern Philippines, including some pupils in primary school and their teachers.
It is the AFP Agency informed, but who spoke to the origin of 65 hostages only.
The 17 children were released after eight hours, as well as a teacher.
The hijacking took place in the province of Agusan del sur.
It is reported that about 19 rebels have used the hostages as human shields during a flight in response to the police.
The local negotiators are trying to find an agreement for the release of the remaining hostages.
According to the AFP Agency, the rebels belong to the New People's Army (NPA), which is the armed wing of the Communist Party of the Philippines (CPP).
According to the AFP Agency, police initially pursued the kidnappers following violence caused during a settling of accounts between two family clans.
Martial law was declared in the province of Maguindanao in the southern Philippines because of a recent massacre in which 57 people were killed.
Among the victims of the massacre of 23 November linked to the election of the administration of Governor there avait30 journalists.
The governor of the province of the southern Philippines was arrested on suspicion of involvement in the massacre, as well as his father Andal Ampatuan, patriarch of the lineage of influential Ampatuan.
The island of Mindanao also includes active Muslim separatists.
They have renewed peace talks with the Philippine government on Tuesday.
