For two years, the only daughter of Liliane Bettencourt has committed criminal proceedings against François-Marie Banier, photographer and artist, which it accuses of having benefited for years from the weakness of his mother to obtain one billion euros in donations, in the form of cheques, contracts of life insurance or tables.
For its part, Liliane Bettencourt has always denied having been manipulated by the photographer, as a longtime friend.
While the court should examine the admissibility of the action taken by Ms. Bettencourt-Meyers, arguments from lawyers have sometimes turned into a large family unpacking Friday.
Thus, the lawyer of Liliane Bettencourt has reported three letters sent by his client (in 1999, 2003 and 2005) to his notary, in which she said to be wary of the husband of Françoise Bettencourt-Meyers.
In the letter dated 2003, Liliane Bettencourt, according to the lawyer added: "Could you explain to my daughter that I wrote to Banier once, twice a day for 15 years.
Françoise, I have never been able to talk to him since his marriage ".
For its part, the prosecutor in Nanterre was again suggested that the complainant was not admissible to act, especially as a juvenile judge refused in recent days to grant his request to open a procedure of judicial protection for his mother.
Liliane Bettencourt "has the ability to sue, it is not under protection and has no guardian.
No one else has to act in his place, "said the representative of the prosecutor, Marie - Chrsitine Daubigney."
The court has finally decided that it would decide once the trial will be held on the admissibility of Mrs Bettencourt-Meyers.
Managerial Revolution or end of the economic intelligence?
If nothing changes in the governance of large French companies, our struggle for the development of economic intelligence will have been in vain...
For more than a decade, the attitude of the management of large companies to its employees, recalls the position of companies from consumers before the revolution marketing: it is to join the staff to "values" determined to as high as it was used to impose the consumer products invented by the technicians from the factory.
By putting the customer at the heart of the company, the revolution has provided marketing strategies of conquest of markets where... although the authoritarian temptation to impose products disconnected factors of preferences of clienteles regularly return!
A demobilization of employees can lead to a deadly demoralisation.
The suicides at France Telecom, PSA and Renault are only the tip of a much broader phenomenon which affects particularly executives.
This demobilization seriously undermines the development of all intellectual functions of the company, including R&D and, more importantly, the economic intelligence.
Indeed, the IE "requires all stakeholders (...) a proactive approach and a forward-looking vision"; it requires on the part of employees a commitment that the authoritarian management revenue blocked completely.
That is why we are calling for a managerial revolution that would put the staff at the centre of the concerns of the company as well as the client.
The relative opinion surveys
The opinion polls as the questionnaire submitted by Orange to its salariés- will push for this revolution in the managerial practices?
Unfortunately, I think not.
- First because I could see that, faced with a new situation, any structure is finally, after many detours, priority... what it has always done.!
- Secondly, because the authoritarianism one of the pathologies of increases in proportion to the importance of its own failures.
- Finally, because most of the leaders have a simplistic view of human behaviour.
From the major engineering schools, they have a mechanistic interpretation of psychology.
They adopt, by intellectual comfort, the old theory behavioural neuroscience "recently reactivated by the" American and widely disseminated, without their knowledge, by institutions and the media.
Thus, suggesting that it is possible to handle the "levers" (sic) the commitment of managers, a recent survey by Ipsos published in Le Figaro.fr conforte-t-elle leaders in a mechanistic governance posture, unsuited to today's world.
Identify the causes of militancy.
On the contrary, the managerial revolution necessary for the proper functioning of modern enterprises, implies a finalist vision of human behaviour.
It is to integrate, in any reasoning or practice of governance, a fundamental observation: for employees, the commitment to the company is only possible if it becomes clear as a means of achieving a portion of their dreams, their ambitions, their projects.
Currently, only studies from the Analysis Motifonctionnelle adopt this design of employees.
These studies have shown that they consider their business based on a predetermined doxa which allows them through their image of the company, to assess what it offers them to achieve their life projects.
Thanks to the identification and the extent of these factors, business managers can control, and anticipate their "social" and their management of human resources "to".
They create a breeding ground for joint development of a robust and effective economic intelligence.
