Thank you
After days roses since last spring, during which the asset inflation was the dominant note on the markets, the uncertainty there arises again, which is not surprising since it comes to their natural state, in an environment where officers take decisions on a future inherently uncertain.
The remedy used by central banks to stabilize markets has been to monetize the debt by the direct purchase of assets and indirectly providing abundant liquidity at rates close to zero, so that financial institutions buy assets to mobilise.
Central banks have already confirmed that the direct purchases of assets were virtually finalised, and without questioning their political maverick of liquidity, begin to put a bit of sand in the wheels, as did the ECB, with their award to a year next week.
Therefore, investors have doubts about the ability of the global economy to maintain an economic recovery without heterodox and we are seeing a reversal of the reduction of risk premiums.
The volatility of stock markets and business obligations are rising again, although they remain very different levels paranormaux they have achieved earlier this year.
The states have been forced to socialize the risk private and public debt is affected.
There is a flight to quality and the United States, Japan and Germany have been selected shelters by investors, an increase of differences between the countries of the euro zone and Germany.
Spain has been barely affected by this episode of instability, but then Standard & Poor his threatened a new downward revision of the qualification of the Kingdom of Spain.
On the other hand, a bit of uncertainty is not bad to silence the defenders of moral hazard, who tried to provoke a new case of conscience in understanding of global economic policy that had hampered the destructive effects of limiting the credit derivatives on the destruction of employment, whereas what should be done is to impose a new Thanksgiving.
However, the situation of Dubai resembles a fight between the tribal sheiks to restore power in the Emirates and we have already seen in the case of Greece.
A government that conceals a public deficit, elections, and a new government who discovers the pot with roses.
Prodi did in Italy after Berlusconi and Socrates in Portugal after Durão Barroso.
It would be perfectly irrational that Ecofin saves Hungary a breach of its external payments at the beginning of the year and allow a member country of the euro area not to meet its commitments.
What makes sense is that Ecofin has prompted the Greek government transparency and makes its citizens share the need for extraordinary measures to maintain the stability of its public finances.
If, as we hope, we are faced with an episode of normalization of risk premiums, after some excesses in high positions, it would be predictable.
In the case of Spain, as long as our differences of public debt is increasing the obligations of European companies, in not to worry about.
If the European and continued to increase, it would be a risk idiosyncratic Spanish.
The Standard & Poor's is an anecdote. When our forward-looking indicators require most services studies to anticipate their models of recovery and to revise their forecasts for 2011, with the OECD and the European Commission, who returned to the office with a Japanese model for the Spanish economy, it does not much hope for their warning.
Again, this appears to be an excellent opportunity to buy assets in Spain, even if for the moment "caution is the mother of safety.
Sectors connected
The chairman of Iberdrola, Ignacio Sánchez Galán, was the first to intervene yesterday, before the subcommittee of the Congress of Deputies, which is discussed these days the energy strategy of Spain for the next two decades.
After his speech, which was followed by the President of Gas Natural-Fenosa, Rafael Villaseca, Mr Galán has outlined for the press that he had raised before the Subcommittee, in camera.
For the president of Iberdrola, Spain needs to invest 50 000 million euros by 2020 and 60 000 million more between then and 2030, where nuclear power plants now in operation would remain open.
If this is not the case, the necessary investments did not rise to 60,000 million but to 95,000.
By contrast, Iberdola considers that for the next decade, investments should not be used to increase production capacity, but distribution networks and interconnections.
From 2020, the question is changing, and it will increase the power.
His bet focuses both gas and coal, with mechanisms for recovery of carbon dioxide and, above all, on renewable energy.
In this area, it considers that 18,000 MW of more are needed, with other energies "support".
Galán, who believes that the draft Law of sustainable economy that the government has approved is in line with what is his company, did not wish to attack the royal decree aimed at encouraging the use of coal, which contradicts the national policies to combat global warming.
According to him, there was "a clear long-term bet" in this sense, despite the measures "one-off" as described the chairman of Iberdrola.
In any event, Galán believes that investment decisions, although they are in the long term, must be taken, because they are some time before reaching maturity and a lucrative stable framework is needed to address them.
