Among other assets, it has the largest wind farm, Waubra (192 MW) in Victoria, and directs the grouping of companies to build and manage the dessalinisateur of Adelaide, with a budget of $700 million.
It now intends to consolidate these two areas and take advantage of synergies to enter markets in the construction and management of infrastructure.
The road toll underground, promoted by the Office of the infrastructure of the city of Brisbane and the Northern Link (north), is called upon to Link the motorway west of Toowong peripheral to Kelvin Grove (see map), by 4 kilometres of tunnel. It is the largest project to reduce traffic congestion in Brisbane.
The timetable set by the administration indicates that the auction will take place during the summer of 2010, and that the work will begin in December next year.
Despite the fact that the toll will be open to traffic at the end of 2014, it is not anticipated that the site is completed before 2016.
The tunnel has begun to be designed in 2005.
It will include two tracks, an electronic toll system and a complex ventilation system.
The Queensland government will provide 500 million Australian dollars (308 million euros) for its funding.
